1
00:00:05.997 --> 00:00:09.476  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
ODO: All right, these barstools
will have to be removed.

2
00:00:09.636 --> 00:00:10.835  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you know how much they cost?

3
00:00:10.916 --> 00:00:12.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No, and I can't say I'm interested
in learning.

4
00:00:13.352 --> 00:00:15.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Station Regulation 2562, paragraph four:

5
00:00:15.634 --> 00:00:17.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"All furniture intended
for use on the Promenade

6
00:00:18.744 --> 00:00:20.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
must not pose a danger to public safety."

7
00:00:20.353 --> 00:00:21.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What danger?

8
00:00:21.313 --> 00:00:22.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
ODO: Without a back on the stool

9
00:00:22.632 --> 00:00:23.912  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Morn could tumble from his perch

10
00:00:23.991 --> 00:00:25.912  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
at any moment, shattering
his upper vertebrae

11
00:00:25.991 --> 00:00:27.791  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
or puncturing three or four of his lungs.

12
00:00:27.870 --> 00:00:28.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nonsense.

13
00:00:29.310 --> 00:00:32.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
His body weight is perfectly distributed
across the seat.

14
00:00:32.470 --> 00:00:35.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's also better able to enjoy the view
of the lovely dabo girls

15
00:00:35.948 --> 00:00:39.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
than he was before
and should he require another drink

16
00:00:39.627 --> 00:00:41.706  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
he need only spin back.

17
00:00:41.947 --> 00:00:43.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Which points out another danger...

18
00:00:43.626 --> 00:00:44.425  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Vertigo.

19
00:00:45.425 --> 00:00:47.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This isn't going to give anybody vertigo.

20
00:00:48.984 --> 00:00:50.944  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your appeal has been heard and rejected.

21
00:00:51.239 --> 00:00:53.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want the barstools removed
by the end of the day.

22
00:00:53.743 --> 00:00:57.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, it's come to my attention
that your dabo wheel is in violation

23
00:00:57.102 --> 00:01:00.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of Station Regulation 4721,
which states...

24
00:01:00.541 --> 00:01:02.101  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-KIRA: Odo.
-Nerys.

25
00:01:02.341 --> 00:01:04.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You busy?
-Not at all.

26
00:01:04.459 --> 00:01:06.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, then can I interest you
in some lunch?

27
00:01:06.339 --> 00:01:07.179  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where shall we go?

28
00:01:07.259 --> 00:01:08.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was thinking
about the Klingon restaurant.

29
00:01:08.858 --> 00:01:10.258  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
KIRA: I haven't been there for ages,

30
00:01:10.378 --> 00:01:12.658  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I have been craving
broiled krada legs.

31
00:01:14.336 --> 00:01:16.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Too bad about the barstools.
I kind of liked them.

32
00:01:16.936 --> 00:01:20.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Did you notice how he changed
the minute she walked into the room?

33
00:01:21.549 --> 00:01:22.935  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-They're in love.
-And what's love?

34
00:01:23.146 --> 00:01:25.254  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Well, it's a--
-Love's a distraction.

35
00:01:26.493 --> 00:01:28.813  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And a distracted policeman is...

36
00:01:30.125 --> 00:01:31.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
An opportunity.

37
00:01:34.371 --> 00:01:37.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
SISKO: <i>Captain's Log,</i> <i>Stardate 51948.3.</i>

38
00:01:37.769 --> 00:01:41.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>With the safe arrival</i>
<i>of Convey PQ-One</i> <i>in the Vegan system</i>

39
00:01:41.369 --> 00:01:44.487  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>our escort duties</i> <i>are now complete</i>
<i>and I've set course for home.</i>

40
00:01:44.568 --> 00:01:48.807  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, my first and hopefully
last mission report for Starfleet Command.

41
00:01:48.886 --> 00:01:52.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, when I first agreed
to be Convoy Liaison Officer

42
00:01:52.286 --> 00:01:55.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought, "Sure, why not?
I know most of the freighter captains

43
00:01:55.565 --> 00:01:57.363  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
in the convoy.
It should be a piece of cake."

44
00:01:57.684 --> 00:02:00.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I didn't know I'd be making 20 log entries

45
00:02:00.163 --> 00:02:02.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
a day and filling out
formal reports every night.

46
00:02:03.562 --> 00:02:05.229  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Looks like you did a pretty good job.

47
00:02:05.241 --> 00:02:07.121  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, if you're going to do something,
do it right.

48
00:02:07.201 --> 00:02:08.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what my father used to say.

49
00:02:09.480 --> 00:02:13.159  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Every father says that. Even I say that.

50
00:02:13.239 --> 00:02:16.918  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's why you're a good parent.
You know all the clichés by heart.

51
00:02:18.517 --> 00:02:21.374  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, hello, stranger.
Haven't seen you in days.

52
00:02:21.117 --> 00:02:23.396  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been filling out
reports for Starfleet Medical.

53
00:02:23.476 --> 00:02:25.876  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I knew there was a reason
why I didn't join Starfleet.

54
00:02:25.955 --> 00:02:27.515  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I--I, I couldn't do this paperwork.

55
00:02:28.747 --> 00:02:28.875  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Smart.

56
00:02:31.513 --> 00:02:33.713  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, there was a time
when you couldn't get him to shut up.

57
00:02:34.273 --> 00:02:35.912  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think I like him better this way.

58
00:02:36.392 --> 00:02:38.592  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-That's mean.
-I was just kidding.

59
00:02:39.231 --> 00:02:41.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No. You weren't.

60
00:02:41.631 --> 00:02:42.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Worf to Captain Sisko.</i>

61
00:02:43.630 --> 00:02:44.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sisko here.

62
00:02:45.109 --> 00:02:48.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
WORF: <i>Sir, can you come to the Bridge?</i>
<i>We have picked up a distress call.</i>

63
00:02:48.828 --> 00:02:49.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
On my way.

64
00:03:00.505 --> 00:03:03.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have been unable
to establish two-way communication so far

65
00:03:03.464 --> 00:03:06.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
WORF: but we have determined
that the signal's coming from somewhere

66
00:03:06.223 --> 00:03:07.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in the Rutharian sector.

67
00:03:08.262 --> 00:03:09.262  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's hear it, Chief.

68
00:03:09.342 --> 00:03:10.542  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beeping )

69
00:03:10.622 --> 00:03:12.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( communication static )

70
00:03:12.261 --> 00:03:15.660  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
WOMAN: <i>and Commander Gatsby's dead, too.</i>
<i>I didn't see any other escape pods leave</i>

71
00:03:15.940 --> 00:03:19.740  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>before the ship was destroyed,</i>
<i>so I may be the only survivor.</i>

72
00:03:19.819 --> 00:03:23.658  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>My pod was torn open on impact</i>
<i>and the rain is pouring in.</i>

73
00:03:24.138 --> 00:03:25.857  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'll take the radio</i>
<i>and a survival kit with me</i>

74
00:03:25.937 --> 00:03:29.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>but the environmental suits were damaged</i>
<i>in the crash, so I-I'll have to rough it.</i>

75
00:03:30.216 --> 00:03:32.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>This is an L-Class world</i>

76
00:03:32.216 --> 00:03:34.815  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and the atmosphere</i>
<i>is barely breathable out there.</i>

77
00:03:35.954 --> 00:03:38.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Repeat, this is a general distress call.</i>

78
00:03:38.973 --> 00:03:41.452  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I am a citizen </i>
<i>of the United Federation of Planets</i>

79
00:03:41.533 --> 00:03:45.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and a Starfleet officer.</i>
<i>If you can hear me, please respond.</i>

80
00:03:45.451 --> 00:03:48.450  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>My government will reward you</i>
<i>for any assistance you can offer</i>

81
00:03:48.531 --> 00:03:52.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and most of all,</i>
<i>you'll be my personal heroes.</i> <i>Repeat...</i>

82
00:03:53.129 --> 00:03:54.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-That's enough.
<i>-This is a general--</i>

83
00:03:55.568 --> 00:03:57.168  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How long will it take us to reach her?

84
00:03:58.128 --> 00:04:00.287  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
At maximum warp, six days.

85
00:04:01.807 --> 00:04:03.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Any other ships closer to that sector?

86
00:04:03.966 --> 00:04:04.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, sir.

87
00:04:05.765 --> 00:04:10.284  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mr. Worf, turn us around
and set a course for the Rutharian sector.

88
00:04:10.763 --> 00:04:11.644  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aye, sir.

89
00:04:14.923 --> 00:04:18.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Chief, I want you to establish
a two-way com link with this woman

90
00:04:19.820 --> 00:04:25.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and when you do, tell her...
tell her her "heroes" are on the way.

91
00:06:21.485 --> 00:06:24.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Captain's Log, supplemental.</i>
<i>The marooned Starfleet officer,</i>

92
00:06:24.564 --> 00:06:28.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>whose name we've</i> <i>learned is Lisa</i>
<i>continues to transmit</i> <i>her call for help</i>

93
00:06:28.282 --> 00:06:32.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>but so far Chief O'Brien</i> <i>has been unable</i>
<i>to establish</i> <i>two-way communication.</i>

94
00:06:32.161 --> 00:06:33.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-How's it going?
-O'BRIEN: Slow.

95
00:06:34.201 --> 00:06:37.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
For some reason, she's transmitting
on a rotating subspace frequency.

96
00:06:37.879 --> 00:06:40.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
We're having a problem
trying to find a way to return her signal.

97
00:06:40.439 --> 00:06:43.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-Do you have to keep that on all the time?
-No, not really.

98
00:06:44.838 --> 00:06:45.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
But she is all alone.

99
00:06:46.277 --> 00:06:47.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
The least I can do
is try and listen to her.

100
00:06:48.316 --> 00:06:50.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
She doesn't know you're listening, Miles.

101
00:06:50.516 --> 00:06:51.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You're not comforting her
by keeping the channels open

102
00:06:52.761 --> 00:06:53.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
and driving yourself crazy.

103
00:06:53.475 --> 00:06:54.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
It doesn't bother me.

104
00:06:54.955 --> 00:06:57.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Sometimes it feels like
she's actually talking to me.

105
00:06:57.634 --> 00:06:59.114  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
LISA: <i>For any assistance you can...</i>

106
00:06:59.193 --> 00:07:00.740  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
It's true.

107
00:07:00.153 --> 00:07:02.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Especially when she talks
about her home or her family.

108
00:07:02.872 --> 00:07:04.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
She reminds me of my cousin.

109
00:07:04.232 --> 00:07:05.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
LISA: <i>Oh, no!</i>

110
00:07:06.191 --> 00:07:09.111  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>I don't believe it. It's raining again.</i>

111
00:07:10.709 --> 00:07:11.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>How can there be so much water</i>
<i>and so little life out there?</i>

112
00:07:12.699 --> 00:07:13.469  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I think I'll leave you two alone.

113
00:07:13.709 --> 00:07:15.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
LISA: <i>I'm really starting</i>
<i>to hate this place.</i>

114
00:07:16.148 --> 00:07:22.266  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>Repeat, this is a general distress call.</i>
<i>Hello? Is anyone paying attention?</i>

115
00:07:22.186 --> 00:07:24.905  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>I know you're out there.</i>
<i>I know you can hear me.</i>

116
00:07:24.986 --> 00:07:28.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>So just answer me.</i>
<i>Tell me you're on your way.</i>

117
00:07:28.945 --> 00:07:32.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Tell me I'm going to be rescued.</i>
<i>Tell me I'm not going to die alone.</i>

118
00:07:43.460 --> 00:07:44.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I hope you're satisfied.

119
00:07:46.820 --> 00:07:49.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sure nothing gives you more pleasure
than stifling my creativity.

120
00:07:49.858 --> 00:07:50.658  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( <i>scoffs </i>)

121
00:07:50.858 --> 00:07:55.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Only you would consider barstools
to be a form of artistic expression.

122
00:07:55.776 --> 00:07:58.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, yeah? Let's see how creative you are.

123
00:07:58.736 --> 00:08:01.735  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Have you... picked out
the Major's gift yet?

124
00:08:03.254 --> 00:08:04.545  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Gift?

125
00:08:05.134 --> 00:08:06.414  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
For this Saturday.

126
00:08:08.372 --> 00:08:10.812  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You do know what Saturday is, right?

127
00:08:12.691 --> 00:08:14.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Saturday?
-Yes.

128
00:08:15.810 --> 00:08:18.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's the one-month anniversary
of your first date with Major Kira.

129
00:08:19.649 --> 00:08:24.768  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Oh... I suppose it is.
-And you haven't picked out a gift.

130
00:08:25.448 --> 00:08:27.876  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why should I?

131
00:08:28.473 --> 00:08:31.646  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The man's experienced unrequited love
for the better part of three years

132
00:08:31.926 --> 00:08:36.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and now that he finally has her
he wants to know why

133
00:08:36.165 --> 00:08:37.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
he should celebrate their anniversary.

134
00:08:37.724 --> 00:08:40.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Whatever you're trying
to sell me, it won't work.

135
00:08:40.123 --> 00:08:42.402  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do you think I'm going to get involved?
No, thank you.

136
00:08:42.483 --> 00:08:44.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The last thing I want to deal with...

137
00:08:44.825 --> 00:08:47.561  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Is a panicked lover looking
for a gift at the last minute.

138
00:08:48.641 --> 00:08:51.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's a whole Promenade
of shopkeepers out there

139
00:08:51.880 --> 00:08:53.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
if you want to buy a gift.

140
00:08:54.199 --> 00:08:58.478  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hmm. A one-month
anniversary gift. ( chuckles )

141
00:08:59.783 --> 00:09:01.237  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Did you ever hear
of anything so ridiculous?

142
00:09:30.308 --> 00:09:32.747  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-JAKE: Okay. So now you--
-Shh!

143
00:09:33.187 --> 00:09:34.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( quietly ) Now you have him
looking for a gift.

144
00:09:34.627 --> 00:09:35.706  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you up to?

145
00:09:36.106 --> 00:09:37.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I tell you, you write it down

146
00:09:37.546 --> 00:09:39.825  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the next thing I know,
I'm in a holding cell.

147
00:09:39.905 --> 00:09:43.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I won't write a word, I promise.
This is just character research.

148
00:09:43.624 --> 00:09:45.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Right.
-Quark, listen.

149
00:09:45.784 --> 00:09:48.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm working on a crime novel
but I've hit a wall in my writing.

150
00:09:48.862 --> 00:09:53.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's... it's not truthful anymore,
phony, artificial.

151
00:09:54.301 --> 00:09:56.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm having trouble creating
real flesh-and-blood characters

152
00:09:57.140 --> 00:10:01.179  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
especially nefarious ones.
If you could just let me

153
00:10:01.259 --> 00:10:05.737  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
watch and listen as you pull off...
whatever it is you're going to pull off,

154
00:10:05.818 --> 00:10:09.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it could really help me out.
You could give me insight.

155
00:10:09.216 --> 00:10:11.775  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I could even model
my lead character after you.

156
00:10:13.535 --> 00:10:18.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Lesson Number One,
No one involved in an extra-legal activity

157
00:10:18.854 --> 00:10:22.413  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-thinks of himself as nefarious.
-Sorry.

158
00:10:22.892 --> 00:10:24.492  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm a businessman, okay?

159
00:10:25.931 --> 00:10:30.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now... if you're interested
in learning more about my business...

160
00:10:32.649 --> 00:10:34.489  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think that could be arranged.

161
00:10:34.928 --> 00:10:35.928  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Great.

162
00:10:40.735 --> 00:10:43.646  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But nothing you see or hear
turns up in print

163
00:10:43.766 --> 00:10:47.245  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and none of it... none of it...
gets back to your father, understand?

164
00:10:48.325 --> 00:10:49.125  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Completely.

165
00:10:49.685 --> 00:10:52.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: <i>So there is a sun after all.</i>

166
00:10:52.838 --> 00:10:54.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Of course, now that the sun is up, </i>
<i>I can see</i>

167
00:10:54.643 --> 00:10:57.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>how truly ugly my new little home is.</i>

168
00:10:57.827 --> 00:10:59.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>There's nothing out there</i>
<i>but dirt and some rocks</i>

169
00:10:59.842 --> 00:11:01.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and some more dirt and some more rocks.</i>

170
00:11:01.800 --> 00:11:02.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Chief?
-Uh-huh?

171
00:11:04.160 --> 00:11:07.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Can I ask you a personal question?
-Sure.

172
00:11:08.559 --> 00:11:11.837  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you uncomfortable
having me aboard the <i>Defiant?</i>

173
00:11:11.918 --> 00:11:15.916  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-No. Why should I be?
-Well, I'm a civilian.

174
00:11:16.236 --> 00:11:18.636  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Isn't it awkward having me
aboard a warship?

175
00:11:18.716 --> 00:11:21.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, we've had civilians aboard before.
Doesn't bother me.

176
00:11:21.715 --> 00:11:23.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was afraid you were going to say that.

177
00:11:23.435 --> 00:11:25.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA : <i>I can hear you! I'm sorry?</i>
<i>Hello? Don't worry about...</i>

178
00:11:25.953 --> 00:11:27.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
O'BRIEN: Hold on a minute.

179
00:11:27.513 --> 00:11:29.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>Receiving your transmission. </i>
<i>Can you hear me?</i>

180
00:11:29.272 --> 00:11:30.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hello?

181
00:11:30.512 --> 00:11:31.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( <i>transmission clears) Hello?</i>

182
00:11:31.872 --> 00:11:34.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I could hear you two talking.</i>
<i>Can you hear me?</i>

183
00:11:34.631 --> 00:11:36.311  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes! Yes, we can hear you.

184
00:11:36.550 --> 00:11:39.549  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Thank God.</i>
<i>Whoever you are, I love you.</i>

185
00:11:40.789 --> 00:11:42.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( laughing )

186
00:11:45.588 --> 00:11:48.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>My name's Lisa Cusak.</i>
<i>Until a couple of days ago,</i>

187
00:11:48.507 --> 00:11:50.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I was the commanding officer</i>
<i>of the </i>Olympia.

188
00:11:50.506 --> 00:11:51.346  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
SISKO: The <i>Olympia?</i>

189
00:11:51.425 --> 00:11:53.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We left the Federation</i>
<i>over eight years ago</i>

190
00:11:53.585 --> 00:11:55.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>for a long-range exploration</i>
<i>of the Beta Quadrant.</i>

191
00:11:56.465 --> 00:11:57.664  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
SISKO: What happened
to your ship, Captain?

192
00:11:57.744 --> 00:12:01.223  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>We were finally heading home,</i>
<i>if you can believe that</i>

193
00:12:01.423 --> 00:12:04.229  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>but then we picked up some strange energy </i>
<i>readings</i> <i>in a nearby star system</i>

194
00:12:04.102 --> 00:12:06.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and I decided to stop and investigate.</i>

195
00:12:07.221 --> 00:12:09.300  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We found an energy barrier</i>
<i>around the fourth planet</i>

196
00:12:09.380 --> 00:12:13.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>that was unlike anything we'd ever seen</i>
<i>and when we probed it with our scanners</i>

197
00:12:13.994 --> 00:12:14.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>it triggered a quantum reaction.</i>

198
00:12:15.379 --> 00:12:17.298  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>There was an enormous surge</i>
<i>of metreon radiation</i>

199
00:12:17.378 --> 00:12:19.577  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>that disabled our engines.</i>
<i>The next thing I knew</i>

200
00:12:19.658 --> 00:12:23.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>we were spiraling in toward the surface.</i>
<i>I gave the order to abandon ship</i>

201
00:12:23.536 --> 00:12:26.735  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and the last thing I remember</i>
<i>is a console exploding in my face.</i>

202
00:12:27.495 --> 00:12:31.494  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I woke up in an escape pod on the surface</i>
<i>and I've spent the last day and a half</i>

203
00:12:31.574 --> 00:12:33.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>sitting in this cave trying</i>
<i>to raise someone on subspace.</i>

204
00:12:34.932 --> 00:12:36.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Captain, Dr. Bashir,
Chief Medical Officer.

205
00:12:36.452 --> 00:12:39.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your message said that you
were on an L-Class planet.

206
00:12:39.451 --> 00:12:40.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Are you sure?
-<i>Positive,</i>

207
00:12:41.509 --> 00:12:42.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and to answer your next question</i>

208
00:12:42.651 --> 00:12:45.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>yes, I've been giving myself</i>
<i>15cc's of tri-ox</i>

209
00:12:45.530 --> 00:12:48.768  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>every four hours to compensate</i>
<i>for the excess carbon dioxide</i>

210
00:12:48.849 --> 00:12:51.928  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>in the atmosphere,</i>
<i>just like it says in my medical tricorder.</i>

211
00:12:52.854 --> 00:12:53.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How much tri-ox do you have left?

212
00:12:53.967 --> 00:12:55.367  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>One hundred and fifty milliliters.</i>

213
00:12:57.206 --> 00:13:02.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Will you reduce the dosage, Captain
to 8cc's every six hours?

214
00:13:02.164 --> 00:13:04.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We need to stretch out
your supply as long as possible.

215
00:13:04.444 --> 00:13:06.643  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What happens when
she runs out of the drug?

216
00:13:06.723 --> 00:13:09.683  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>That's a good question,</i>
<i>Doctor. What happens then?</i>

217
00:13:09.762 --> 00:13:12.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You will begin to experience
the effects of hypoxia

218
00:13:13.141 --> 00:13:15.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but before that happens,
the tri-ox compound

219
00:13:15.360 --> 00:13:18.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
will have strengthened
your cardiopulmonary system

220
00:13:18.160 --> 00:13:19.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
allowing you to better
withstand the effects.

221
00:13:20.798 --> 00:13:21.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: <i>"Better withstand the effects."</i>

222
00:13:22.318 --> 00:13:24.678  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>In other words,</i>
<i>I'm going to be gasping for air</i>

223
00:13:24.758 --> 00:13:27.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and turning different shades </i>
<i>of blue by the time you get here.</i>

224
00:13:28.757 --> 00:13:29.996  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, I'm afraid so.

225
00:13:30.397 --> 00:13:31.876  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: <i>Thanks for brightening my day.</i>

226
00:13:32.758 --> 00:13:35.914  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is there anything we can do?
-<i>There is, actually. I can't sleep.</i>

227
00:13:35.995 --> 00:13:37.914  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I--I think the injections </i>
<i>are keeping me awake</i>

228
00:13:38.233 --> 00:13:40.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and I haven't had anyone</i>
<i>to talk to for two days.</i>

229
00:13:40.393 --> 00:13:42.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'll be able to help you
with that, Captain.

230
00:13:42.752 --> 00:13:44.192  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll have one of my officers

231
00:13:44.272 --> 00:13:47.191  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
stay on the com line
with you at all times.

232
00:13:47.272 --> 00:13:49.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>And order them to enjoy it, too.</i>

233
00:13:49.390 --> 00:13:50.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Done.

234
00:13:51.310 --> 00:13:52.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>So, who's first?</i>

235
00:13:54.229 --> 00:13:55.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think I'd better start.

236
00:13:55.349 --> 00:13:56.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sounds good to me.

237
00:13:58.628 --> 00:14:02.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A lot has happened...
since you left, Captain.

238
00:14:06.345 --> 00:14:08.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
SISKO: The Second Fleet hit
the Dominion forces

239
00:14:08.305 --> 00:14:10.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
occupying Betazed three
times in the last month

240
00:14:10.664 --> 00:14:12.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but they keep sending in reinforcements

241
00:14:12.783 --> 00:14:14.943  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and fortifying their positions,
so we find it--

242
00:14:15.231 --> 00:14:16.231  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: <i>Okay, okay...</i>

243
00:14:16.102 --> 00:14:17.422  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( coughing )

244
00:14:17.502 --> 00:14:20.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's it, please. No more war news.
You're depressing me.

245
00:14:20.661 --> 00:14:22.140  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, sorry.

246
00:14:22.980 --> 00:14:25.180  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: <i>No. I'm sorry.</i>

247
00:14:25.259 --> 00:14:28.459  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'm sorry for you and me</i>
<i>and everyone in the Federation.</i>

248
00:14:28.539 --> 00:14:31.180  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I can't believe we're at war.</i>

249
00:14:31.986 --> 00:14:34.537  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Let's change the subject.</i>
<i>How about some good news?</i>

250
00:14:34.617 --> 00:14:37.536  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Tell me there's still something</i>
<i>to look forward to when I get home.</i>

251
00:14:38.256 --> 00:14:41.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Tell me people still fall in love</i>
<i>and get married and raise families.</i>

252
00:14:42.414 --> 00:14:43.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They do.

253
00:14:43.534 --> 00:14:46.373  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>Good, and what about you?</i>
<i>Are you married?</i>

254
00:14:46.933 --> 00:14:47.853  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

255
00:14:48.333 --> 00:14:49.132  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: <i>Seeing anyone?</i>

256
00:14:49.292 --> 00:14:50.732  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I mean, I hate to pry</i>
<i>but I'd like to think</i>

257
00:14:50.812 --> 00:14:52.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>that there's still something positive</i>

258
00:14:52.411 --> 00:14:54.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>in the life of a starship captain </i>
<i>these days.</i>

259
00:14:54.914 --> 00:14:55.131  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

260
00:14:55.251 --> 00:14:57.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am seeing someone.

261
00:14:57.570 --> 00:15:00.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>Oh, now we're talking.</i>
<i>Tell me about her. What's her name?</i>

262
00:15:01.569 --> 00:15:02.448  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kasidy Yates.

263
00:15:03.880 --> 00:15:06.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Kasidy? Is she the same Kasidy
I spoke to earlier?

264
00:15:06.247 --> 00:15:08.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-That's her.
-<i>She one of your officers?</i>

265
00:15:08.687 --> 00:15:12.246  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No. Civilian. Freighter Captain.

266
00:15:12.806 --> 00:15:15.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: Uh-oh. <i>Sounds like</i>
<i>you're having problems.</i>

267
00:15:16.205 --> 00:15:17.764  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why would you say something like that?

268
00:15:17.844 --> 00:15:20.643  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>There's no joy in that voice </i>
<i>of yours, Ben.</i>

269
00:15:21.163 --> 00:15:23.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>In fact, the tension level</i>
<i>went up when you said her name.</i>

270
00:15:23.402 --> 00:15:26.419  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You sounded more relaxed</i>
<i>when you were telling me about the war.</i>

271
00:15:29.720 --> 00:15:31.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Ben, are you still there?</i>

272
00:15:32.159 --> 00:15:33.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) Yes.

273
00:15:34.519 --> 00:15:37.798  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, I'm still here. You just...

274
00:15:39.398 --> 00:15:43.237  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
caught me off-guard... a little.

275
00:15:44.116 --> 00:15:45.156  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: <i>I can tell.</i>

276
00:15:45.556 --> 00:15:49.474  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, back when I was a junior officer
I dated a civilian for six years.

277
00:15:49.555 --> 00:15:51.474  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( coughing ) <i>Want to hear about it?</i>

278
00:15:51.554 --> 00:15:52.394  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Sure you do.</i>

279
00:15:52.753 --> 00:15:56.912  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Why? Because it's a funny story</i>
<i>and one of us needs to cheer up.</i>

280
00:15:57.112 --> 00:15:58.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>So, we met on Andor.</i>

281
00:15:58.992 --> 00:16:01.751  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I was assigned to the Federation</i>
<i>Embassy as an attaché</i>

282
00:16:01.831 --> 00:16:04.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and he was working in the Andorian </i>
<i>Agricultural Ministry.</i>

283
00:16:04.550 --> 00:16:06.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Now, at first, I didn't want anything </i>
<i>to do with him.</i>

284
00:16:06.869 --> 00:16:09.549  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>He kept pointing his antennae at me</i>
<i>whenever I walked through his office</i>

285
00:16:09.628 --> 00:16:11.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and I found that sort of rude.</i>

286
00:16:12.828 --> 00:16:16.506  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
QUARK: Excuse me... coming through.
Excuse me, excuse me...

287
00:16:16.586 --> 00:16:17.386  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Odo.

288
00:16:17.826 --> 00:16:20.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well... this is it.

289
00:16:21.185 --> 00:16:22.254  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can I see it?

290
00:16:26.584 --> 00:16:29.662  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh... very nice.

291
00:16:30.702 --> 00:16:32.223  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Major's gonna love it.

292
00:16:34.181 --> 00:16:35.660  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How are you gonna give it to her?

293
00:16:37.220 --> 00:16:39.460  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What sort of evening do you have planned?

294
00:16:40.299 --> 00:16:41.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't have anything planned.

295
00:16:42.192 --> 00:16:45.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh... fortunately for you,
there's still time.

296
00:16:51.536 --> 00:16:52.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Pick one.

297
00:16:52.896 --> 00:16:54.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A holosuite program?

298
00:16:54.575 --> 00:16:57.614  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's your anniversary.
You have to do something special.

299
00:16:58.254 --> 00:16:59.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I bought her a gift.

300
00:17:01.972 --> 00:17:05.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have it your way. But if it were me

301
00:17:05.372 --> 00:17:08.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I had found true love
after a lifetime of searching...

302
00:17:09.891 --> 00:17:12.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
every month would be worth celebrating.

303
00:17:14.649 --> 00:17:15.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
ODO: All right.

304
00:17:15.808 --> 00:17:17.688  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let me look at those programs.

305
00:17:18.803 --> 00:17:19.168  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
ODO: Come on.

306
00:17:32.244 --> 00:17:35.163  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Looks like the Constable's
going to be busy Saturday night.

307
00:17:35.763 --> 00:17:36.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I guess that means

308
00:17:36.883 --> 00:17:38.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
he won't be following
me around the station

309
00:17:39.421 --> 00:17:41.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or watching the airlocks
for wanted criminals

310
00:17:41.481 --> 00:17:44.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or monitoring the cargo bays
for illegal transactions.

311
00:17:44.920 --> 00:17:46.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, he has deputies.

312
00:17:47.239 --> 00:17:50.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Deputies, I can handle.
With Odo out of the way

313
00:17:50.479 --> 00:17:52.877  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
my biggest problem will be deciding...

314
00:17:53.837 --> 00:17:56.116  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
what to do with all the money
I'm going to make!

315
00:17:56.637 --> 00:18:00.636  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>Both my sisters are teachers.</i>
<i>I don't know how they can do it.</i>

316
00:18:00.715 --> 00:18:02.754  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Personally, I can't stand children.</i>

317
00:18:02.834 --> 00:18:03.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh-huh.

318
00:18:04.742 --> 00:18:06.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>I know, I know,</i>
<i>everybody loves children.</i>

319
00:18:06.873 --> 00:18:07.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Not me.</i>

320
00:18:08.113 --> 00:18:08.913  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( distracted ) Yeah.

321
00:18:09.233 --> 00:18:11.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>What about you? You like children?</i>

322
00:18:11.552 --> 00:18:12.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, yeah.

323
00:18:13.751 --> 00:18:14.591  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( unconvinced ) <i>Really?</i>

324
00:18:15.431 --> 00:18:16.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah.

325
00:18:16.351 --> 00:18:19.869  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You know, Doctor, I'm starting to think</i>
<i>that maybe, just maybe</i>

326
00:18:20.298 --> 00:18:21.549  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>you're not really paying attention to--</i>

327
00:18:22.748 --> 00:18:23.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Wait a minute.</i>

328
00:18:24.108 --> 00:18:27.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>What's that?</i>
<i>There's something moving out there.</i>

329
00:18:29.107 --> 00:18:30.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>It's getting closer.</i>

330
00:18:30.507 --> 00:18:31.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
BASHIR: What?

331
00:18:31.546 --> 00:18:35.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>Stay back.</i>
( terrified ) <i>No. Don't hurt me.</i>

332
00:18:35.385 --> 00:18:36.624  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain, what's going on?

333
00:18:36.744 --> 00:18:41.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( sobbing ) <i>Please, stay back.</i>
<i>No, don't...</i> ( screaming ) <i>No!</i>

334
00:18:48.821 --> 00:18:51.300  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain Cusak, can you hear me? Hello?

335
00:18:54.739 --> 00:18:56.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hello? God...

336
00:18:57.458 --> 00:18:58.898  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
DEEP VOICE: <i>She's gone.</i>

337
00:18:58.978 --> 00:19:00.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
BASHIR: Who is this?

338
00:19:00.497 --> 00:19:01.656  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What have you done?

339
00:19:01.737 --> 00:19:03.576  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
DEEP VOICE: <i>I have eaten her.</i>

340
00:19:03.817 --> 00:19:04.616  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?

341
00:19:04.776 --> 00:19:07.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
DEEP VOICE: <i>I've eaten her!</i>
<i>What difference does it make to you?</i>

342
00:19:08.335 --> 00:19:14.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You weren't even listening to her.</i>
You have my sincere apologies.

343
00:19:15.893 --> 00:19:17.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was carried away with my work.

344
00:19:17.452 --> 00:19:20.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>I'm a patient, aren't I?</i>
<i>Doesn't that make me part of your work?</i>

345
00:19:20.811 --> 00:19:22.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
BASHIR: You're right,
you're absolutely right.

346
00:19:22.770 --> 00:19:24.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know what I was thinking.

347
00:19:25.770 --> 00:19:27.929  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You now have my complete attention.

348
00:19:28.489 --> 00:19:29.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: ( sighs )

349
00:19:29.449 --> 00:19:32.807  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Well, I've got news for you, Doc.</i>
<i>I'm all talked out.</i>

350
00:19:33.820 --> 00:19:35.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It's time for you</i>
<i>to cheer up one of your patients</i>

351
00:19:35.367 --> 00:19:36.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and take her mind off her impending doom.</i>

352
00:19:36.966 --> 00:19:38.286  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're not doomed.

353
00:19:38.366 --> 00:19:39.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: <i>I feel better already.</i>

354
00:19:40.245 --> 00:19:42.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>See how easy that was? Now keep going.</i>

355
00:19:43.364 --> 00:19:45.444  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
BASHIR: Oh, what should I talk about?

356
00:19:45.724 --> 00:19:47.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>How did they let you</i>
<i>out of medical school</i>

357
00:19:47.843 --> 00:19:51.826  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>with this kind of bedside manner?</i>
<i>Are you sure you're a doctor?</i>

358
00:19:51.482 --> 00:19:53.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
BASHIR: Yes, I graduated
second in my class, in fact.

359
00:19:54.413 --> 00:19:56.881  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>Oh. And we're especially</i>
<i>proud of that, aren't we?</i>

360
00:19:58.920 --> 00:20:01.479  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I get the feeling that
it's going to take me some hours

361
00:20:01.559 --> 00:20:03.599  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to crawl out of this rather sizable hole

362
00:20:03.758 --> 00:20:04.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've dug for myself.

363
00:20:04.918 --> 00:20:07.597  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: <i>Not at all. It'll take you days.</i>

364
00:20:11.436 --> 00:20:14.475  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have my personal assurance
they're high-quality crystals

365
00:20:14.555 --> 00:20:17.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you won't get them at this price
anywhere else in the Quadrant.

366
00:20:17.754 --> 00:20:18.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( coughs )

367
00:20:22.712 --> 00:20:24.592  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( softly ) Five days,
Cargo Bay 3. See you then.

368
00:20:28.551 --> 00:20:29.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll take this one.

369
00:20:30.550 --> 00:20:35.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah... "Paris, 1928." Nice choice.

370
00:20:35.749 --> 00:20:39.468  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Say what you will about humans today,
their past was certainly...

371
00:20:39.547 --> 00:20:40.507  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( whispering ) romantic.

372
00:20:40.587 --> 00:20:43.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, book us four hours
starting at 2100 on Sunday night.

373
00:20:43.546 --> 00:20:44.666  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You mean Saturday.

374
00:20:45.786 --> 00:20:47.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean Sunday.

375
00:20:48.651 --> 00:20:50.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But Saturday's the anniversary
of your first date.

376
00:20:50.185 --> 00:20:53.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes, but our first date ended badly.
It's not something I want to commemorate

377
00:20:53.943 --> 00:20:57.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so I've decided to celebrate
the anniversary of our first kiss.

378
00:20:57.782 --> 00:21:01.217  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Your first kiss?
-Romantic, isn't it? ( chuckles )

379
00:21:01.101 --> 00:21:01.981  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aw...

380
00:21:08.939 --> 00:21:10.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beeping )

381
00:21:10.738 --> 00:21:11.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come on.

382
00:21:12.580 --> 00:21:13.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beeping )

383
00:21:13.982 --> 00:21:14.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come on.

384
00:21:14.218 --> 00:21:15.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beeping continues )

385
00:21:15.177 --> 00:21:17.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What's going on?
-QUARK: My partner,

386
00:21:17.536 --> 00:21:19.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't get him on the channel.

387
00:21:19.216 --> 00:21:20.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

388
00:21:20.656 --> 00:21:24.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-He's changed his com system protocols.
-Already? You just talked to him.

389
00:21:25.574 --> 00:21:27.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's a wanted man, Jake.
He has to be very careful

390
00:21:27.813 --> 00:21:30.572  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
about how often he uses subspace.
The authorities might try

391
00:21:30.653 --> 00:21:31.771  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and trace his signal.

392
00:21:32.652 --> 00:21:33.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

393
00:21:34.571 --> 00:21:38.970  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have no way of contacting him
until he gets here Saturday night.

394
00:21:39.497 --> 00:21:41.489  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, can't you just explain
to him that he'll have to wait

395
00:21:41.569 --> 00:21:42.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
another day?

396
00:21:42.529 --> 00:21:45.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Haven't you been paying attention?
If he even sets foot on the station

397
00:21:45.688 --> 00:21:48.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
while Odo's on duty,
we'll both be in a holding cell

398
00:21:48.167 --> 00:21:50.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
faster than you can say
"criminal conspiracy."

399
00:21:50.886 --> 00:21:52.446  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

400
00:21:54.445 --> 00:21:56.535  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then, what are you going to do?

401
00:21:56.644 --> 00:21:57.564  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Th--think.

402
00:21:58.444 --> 00:22:01.883  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My best option is, uh... um...

403
00:22:02.802 --> 00:22:03.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Panic.

404
00:22:04.322 --> 00:22:05.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

405
00:22:10.320 --> 00:22:12.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When the fighting first
broke out, I thought to myself

406
00:22:12.919 --> 00:22:14.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"All right, O'Brien,
you've done this before.

407
00:22:17.198 --> 00:22:19.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"Keep your head down...

408
00:22:19.478 --> 00:22:23.767  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"focus on the job
and you'll get through this,

409
00:22:23.157 --> 00:22:24.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
just like you did in the last war."

410
00:22:25.955 --> 00:22:27.355  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But this war is different.

411
00:22:27.835 --> 00:22:29.435  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckling ) Maybe I'm different.

412
00:22:31.994 --> 00:22:32.994  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have this...

413
00:22:33.714 --> 00:22:37.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This growing sense of isolation.
I see people.

414
00:22:37.512 --> 00:22:40.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I... talk to them,
I laugh with them, and...

415
00:22:40.511 --> 00:22:43.311  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But some part of me is always saying...

416
00:22:47.150 --> 00:22:48.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"They may not be here tomorrow.

417
00:22:50.748 --> 00:22:51.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't get too close."

418
00:22:54.187 --> 00:22:56.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry. I... I'm sorry,

419
00:22:56.946 --> 00:22:58.866  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I shouldn't be laying
all this on your shoulders, Captain.

420
00:22:58.946 --> 00:23:01.945  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA:<i> No, no, it's all right,</i>
<i>Miles. I don't mind.</i>

421
00:23:02.251 --> 00:23:04.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Sounds like you really need</i>
<i>to talk with someone about this.</i>

422
00:23:04.104 --> 00:23:06.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sure it's the last thing
you need to hear.

423
00:23:06.383 --> 00:23:08.543  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I should be cheering you up.

424
00:23:08.623 --> 00:23:11.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Forget about me.</i>
<i>You're the one who needs cheering up.</i>

425
00:23:11.902 --> 00:23:13.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

426
00:23:13.421 --> 00:23:15.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, there's a sad state of affairs.

427
00:23:15.341 --> 00:23:18.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Look, you've seen a lot</i>
<i>of combat in the last year.</i>

428
00:23:18.100 --> 00:23:20.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>That's a heavy burden to carry around.</i>

429
00:23:20.939 --> 00:23:23.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you sure you're a Captain,
not a Counselor?

430
00:23:23.499 --> 00:23:24.898  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: <i>Oh, I'm sure.</i>

431
00:23:24.978 --> 00:23:27.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I'll let you in on a little secret, Miles.</i>

432
00:23:27.977 --> 00:23:29.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I dislike the whole concept</i>
<i>of a ship's counselor.</i>

433
00:23:30.497 --> 00:23:31.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Me, too.

434
00:23:31.416 --> 00:23:33.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I mean, I--I like some of them
personally, but--

435
00:23:33.655 --> 00:23:35.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>But sometimes</i>
<i>they just get in the way.</i>

436
00:23:36.775 --> 00:23:40.373  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's exactly how I feel,
but saying it out loud is almost heresy.

437
00:23:41.373 --> 00:23:43.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And there's this assumption
nowadays that...

438
00:23:43.773 --> 00:23:45.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
only someone with a diploma

439
00:23:46.117 --> 00:23:48.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
can listen to your problems
or give you advice.

440
00:23:48.771 --> 00:23:50.771  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>Sometimes, all you need</i>
<i>are good friends.</i>

441
00:23:50.850 --> 00:23:51.970  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Exactly.

442
00:23:52.500 --> 00:23:53.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: <i>So where are they?</i>

443
00:23:53.449 --> 00:23:54.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What? Excuse me?

444
00:23:54.889 --> 00:23:58.128  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>Where are your friends, Miles?</i>
<i>Why aren't they helping you through this?</i>

445
00:24:00.727 --> 00:24:02.567  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, we, uh...

446
00:24:02.726 --> 00:24:05.468  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I haven't spoken to them
about any of this.

447
00:24:05.566 --> 00:24:07.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, it's not the kind
of thing you talk about.

448
00:24:08.245 --> 00:24:11.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>Hmm. Well, if you can't</i>
<i>talk to your friends</i>

449
00:24:11.964 --> 00:24:15.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you can't talk to your wife,
you know who that leaves.

450
00:24:16.403 --> 00:24:18.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-A ship's counselor.
-<i>A ship's counselor.</i>

451
00:24:18.122 --> 00:24:19.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( Cusak coughing )

452
00:24:20.242 --> 00:24:22.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
BASHIR: <i>Excuse me, but it's 1800 hours.</i>

453
00:24:22.561 --> 00:24:23.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Already?

454
00:24:23.720 --> 00:24:24.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Afraid so.

455
00:24:24.960 --> 00:24:26.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
O'BRIEN: But we're still talking.

456
00:24:26.359 --> 00:24:28.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: <i>Boys, boys, don't fight over me.</i>

457
00:24:28.519 --> 00:24:30.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( coughing ) <i>Miles, I'll talk to you </i>
<i>in the morning.</i>

458
00:24:30.758 --> 00:24:32.278  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And think about what I said.

459
00:24:33.477 --> 00:24:38.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All right.
And I will. Good night, Captain.

460
00:24:38.436 --> 00:24:39.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: <i>Good night.</i>

461
00:24:41.475 --> 00:24:43.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Well, Julian, don't let me</i>
<i>keep you from your work.</i>

462
00:24:43.435 --> 00:24:44.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I know how busy you are.</i>

463
00:24:45.434 --> 00:24:46.633  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No work tonight.

464
00:24:46.714 --> 00:24:49.873  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>Oh! So you've decided</i>
<i>to spend your valuable time</i>

465
00:24:49.952 --> 00:24:53.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>conversing with your patient again.</i>
<i>That's three days in a row.</i>

466
00:24:53.231 --> 00:24:55.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You must be swamped with paperwork by now.</i>

467
00:24:55.431 --> 00:24:58.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I feel awful, keeping you</i>
<i>from your duties like this.</i>

468
00:24:58.270 --> 00:25:00.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I managed to catch up
with all my paperwork this afternoon

469
00:25:00.229 --> 00:25:01.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
thank you very much.

470
00:25:01.269 --> 00:25:02.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: <i>Let me guess,</i>

471
00:25:02.908 --> 00:25:05.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>thanks to your amazing</i>
<i>genetically engineered brain</i>

472
00:25:06.677 --> 00:25:07.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>you not only did your work</i>

473
00:25:07.667 --> 00:25:10.267  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>you did the work of ten</i>
<i>other doctors at the same time.</i>

474
00:25:10.346 --> 00:25:11.146  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well?

475
00:25:11.906 --> 00:25:13.656  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But you've answered the next question

476
00:25:13.146 --> 00:25:15.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was going to ask you,
which is "how are you feeling?"

477
00:25:15.705 --> 00:25:18.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can hear that you're in your usual
acerbic good mood.

478
00:25:18.704 --> 00:25:21.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: <i>Wrong again, my superhuman friend.</i>

479
00:25:21.703 --> 00:25:24.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>As a matter of fact,</i>
<i>I'm not feeling well at all.</i>

480
00:25:24.502 --> 00:25:25.502  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell me.

481
00:25:26.142 --> 00:25:28.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>The last injection</i>
<i>didn't do the trick.</i>

482
00:25:28.541 --> 00:25:32.300  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I feel this heavy weight on my chest.</i>
<i>It's getting harder to breathe</i>

483
00:25:33.604 --> 00:25:36.139  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and every time I move my head,</i>
<i>the cave starts spinning.</i>

484
00:25:37.179 --> 00:25:38.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( <i>door chimes </i>)

485
00:25:38.138 --> 00:25:39.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
SISKO: Come in.

486
00:25:40.897 --> 00:25:41.817  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is it?

487
00:25:41.937 --> 00:25:43.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain Cusak's run out of tri-ox.

488
00:25:43.976 --> 00:25:46.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She's beginning to feel
the effects of CO2 poisoning.

489
00:25:46.956 --> 00:25:46.896  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Already?

490
00:25:47.255 --> 00:25:50.134  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought she had at least
a day's worth of injections left.

491
00:25:50.214 --> 00:25:51.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So did I, but apparently the last vial

492
00:25:52.140 --> 00:25:54.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
was tainted somehow,
probably in the crash.

493
00:25:54.133 --> 00:25:57.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-How long does she have?
-No more than two days.

494
00:25:59.120 --> 00:26:02.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's not good.
We're still three days away.

495
00:26:10.209 --> 00:26:13.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-We need more speed.
-Speed's not the problem.

496
00:26:13.884 --> 00:26:15.607  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I could increase
the warp plasma 97 gigahertz.

497
00:26:15.687 --> 00:26:20.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That would increase our velocity to warp
9.5 and save us almost a full day.

498
00:26:20.326 --> 00:26:21.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WORF: The problem on the <i>Defiant </i>is

499
00:26:21.405 --> 00:26:24.444  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
how to maintain structural integrity
when we go above warp nine.

500
00:26:24.604 --> 00:26:26.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Exactly. At those kind of speeds

501
00:26:26.403 --> 00:26:28.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the ship literally starts
tearing herself apart.

502
00:26:28.923 --> 00:26:31.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Is there any way to strengthen
the structural integrity field?

503
00:26:31.722 --> 00:26:33.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not without bleeding power
from some other source.

504
00:26:33.961 --> 00:26:34.881  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
SISKO: Such as?

505
00:26:35.361 --> 00:26:37.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-The phaser reserves.
-WORF: That would be unwise.

506
00:26:37.481 --> 00:26:38.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If we empty the defense reserves

507
00:26:38.960 --> 00:26:40.559  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we could find ourselves
at an extreme disadvantage

508
00:26:40.640 --> 00:26:42.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
should we encounter a Dominion ship.

509
00:26:42.519 --> 00:26:44.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're a long way from the front lines
out here, Worf.

510
00:26:44.518 --> 00:26:46.877  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The chances of meeting
a Dominion ship are negligible.

511
00:26:46.958 --> 00:26:48.517  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We should not take that risk.

512
00:26:48.597 --> 00:26:51.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She'll die if we do not get to her faster.

513
00:26:55.194 --> 00:26:57.994  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Use the phaser reserve, Chief.
Give us all the speed you can.

514
00:26:58.741 --> 00:26:59.593  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aye, sir. Thank you, sir.

515
00:27:07.720 --> 00:27:08.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How's it going?

516
00:27:08.591 --> 00:27:10.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're increasing speed.

517
00:27:10.231 --> 00:27:12.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Captain's condition is worsening.

518
00:27:12.629 --> 00:27:13.469  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I see.

519
00:27:13.989 --> 00:27:16.429  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is there anything I can do?
-I don't think so.

520
00:27:18.188 --> 00:27:20.787  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I guess I'll see you later.

521
00:27:20.867 --> 00:27:23.266  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Right.
-Right.

522
00:27:30.385 --> 00:27:32.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you sure you want to hear about this?

523
00:27:32.264 --> 00:27:33.783  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: ( weakly ) <i>Trust me, Ben.</i>

524
00:27:33.863 --> 00:27:35.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'd much rather be worrying</i>
<i>about your love life</i>

525
00:27:36.627 --> 00:27:37.662  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>than about my own problems right now.</i>

526
00:27:37.742 --> 00:27:40.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( coughing )

527
00:27:40.861 --> 00:27:45.140  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, when Kasidy came
to the Bridge last night

528
00:27:45.420 --> 00:27:50.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
all I wanted her to do was leave
and I couldn't tell you why.

529
00:27:50.539 --> 00:27:54.217  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
LISA: <i>She doesn't belong there, Ben. </i>
<i>That's why.</i>

530
00:27:54.297 --> 00:27:57.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>She doesn't belong in that part</i>
<i>of your life, and you know it.</i>

531
00:27:57.816 --> 00:28:01.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Off duty, I'm sure Kasidy</i>
<i>is exactly what you need</i>

532
00:28:01.255 --> 00:28:03.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>but on the Defiant,</i>
<i>she's a random element...</i>

533
00:28:04.545 --> 00:28:05.454  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( coughs )

534
00:28:05.533 --> 00:28:08.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>a piece that doesn't fit</i>
<i>anywhere in the puzzle.</i>

535
00:28:10.413 --> 00:28:12.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

536
00:28:12.292 --> 00:28:15.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She was the Convoy Liaison
Officer on our last mission

537
00:28:15.891 --> 00:28:17.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and a damned good one, too.

538
00:28:17.650 --> 00:28:19.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LISA: <i>This isn't about her.</i>

539
00:28:20.504 --> 00:28:21.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>This is about you.</i>

540
00:28:21.609 --> 00:28:23.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You're having trouble doing your job</i>

541
00:28:23.648 --> 00:28:26.168  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>when she's on the Defiant,</i>
<i>and that's a problem.</i>

542
00:28:26.247 --> 00:28:30.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It's also affecting your relationship</i>
<i>and that's another problem.</i>

543
00:28:30.607 --> 00:28:32.366  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Don't take it so hard.</i>

544
00:28:32.446 --> 00:28:35.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>So, you can't mix your personal</i>
<i>life and your professional life.</i>

545
00:28:35.965 --> 00:28:37.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Most people can't.</i>

546
00:28:37.885 --> 00:28:39.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I certainly can't.</i>

547
00:28:39.924 --> 00:28:42.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I once served on the same</i>
<i>starbase as my sister.</i>

548
00:28:42.923 --> 00:28:44.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Oh, what a nightmare that was.</i>

549
00:28:44.642 --> 00:28:45.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( coughs )

550
00:28:45.922 --> 00:28:48.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I look forward to meeting you, Lisa.

551
00:28:48.361 --> 00:28:52.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sure I'm not the only one
around here who feels the same way.

552
00:28:52.600 --> 00:28:53.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>If you ask me...</i>

553
00:28:53.999 --> 00:28:55.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( coughs )

554
00:28:55.399 --> 00:28:58.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Everyone on that ship could use some R&amp;R.</i>

555
00:28:58.838 --> 00:29:00.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( coughing )

556
00:29:06.595 --> 00:29:07.756  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Beautiful, aren't they?

557
00:29:08.595 --> 00:29:09.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Gorgeous.

558
00:29:11.314 --> 00:29:13.114  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do you know how much
I was going to get for these?

559
00:29:14.553 --> 00:29:15.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Almost 200 bars.

560
00:29:16.633 --> 00:29:19.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-That's a lot.
-No kidding. That's a lot.

561
00:29:20.311 --> 00:29:23.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now... they're just a crate full of junk.

562
00:29:25.390 --> 00:29:28.509  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, there's still a chance
that Odo won't find out about any of this.

563
00:29:28.749 --> 00:29:31.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, he'll find out.

564
00:29:33.268 --> 00:29:36.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Odo would love nothing better
than to see me in jail.

565
00:29:38.268 --> 00:29:39.706  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And after all I did for him.

566
00:29:40.226 --> 00:29:41.346  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Like what?

567
00:29:43.825 --> 00:29:46.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Like helping him find true love.

568
00:29:47.640 --> 00:29:49.622  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's right. If it wasn't for me

569
00:29:49.703 --> 00:29:51.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
he and Major Kira
would never have gotten together

570
00:29:51.582 --> 00:29:52.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in the first place.

571
00:29:54.382 --> 00:29:55.741  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was there for him

572
00:29:55.981 --> 00:29:58.660  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
during all the heartache
and the lonely nights.

573
00:29:59.260 --> 00:30:02.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When he was wallowing in misery
because she was still seeing Shakaar.

574
00:30:03.659 --> 00:30:05.178  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I told him to make his move.

575
00:30:07.337 --> 00:30:09.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I told him not to give up.

576
00:30:11.657 --> 00:30:12.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was there for him.

577
00:30:15.855 --> 00:30:21.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And what did I get out of it? Nothing.
He still spies on me. He still bothers me

578
00:30:21.973 --> 00:30:23.932  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
about minor infractions of the law.

579
00:30:25.452 --> 00:30:28.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And he still can't wait
for the opportunity

580
00:30:28.491 --> 00:30:29.930  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to send me to prison.

581
00:30:34.489 --> 00:30:37.928  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I should have remembered
the 285th Rule of Acquisition.

582
00:30:41.128 --> 00:30:44.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"No good deed ever goes unpunished."

583
00:31:27.353 --> 00:31:30.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
To failure.
I'm not drinking to that.

584
00:31:30.832 --> 00:31:36.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Jake, in ten minutes
my business partner's ship will dock.

585
00:31:36.550 --> 00:31:39.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In 15 minutes, Odo will arrest him.

586
00:31:39.350 --> 00:31:41.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In 20 minutes, my name will come up.

587
00:31:42.469 --> 00:31:46.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And in 25 minutes, Odo will walk
in here with a warrant.

588
00:31:48.627 --> 00:31:50.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think you should humor me on this one.

589
00:32:04.862 --> 00:32:06.219  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Quark...

590
00:32:06.861 --> 00:32:09.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd like that holosuite now after all.

591
00:32:10.260 --> 00:32:12.220  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You would.
-QUARK: That's right.

592
00:32:12.580 --> 00:32:17.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Turns out Nerys agrees with you.
She wants to celebrate the anniversary

593
00:32:17.779 --> 00:32:20.577  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of our first date, not our first kiss.
So here we are.

594
00:32:22.137 --> 00:32:24.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is the holosuite still available?

595
00:32:24.936 --> 00:32:27.656  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's, um... it's all yours.

596
00:32:29.295 --> 00:32:30.815  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The program?

597
00:32:41.891 --> 00:32:43.509  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Odo?

598
00:32:44.610 --> 00:32:45.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have a good time.

599
00:32:45.730 --> 00:32:47.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Thank you, Quark.
I'm sure we will.

600
00:32:51.128 --> 00:32:53.688  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I don't believe it.
-Neither do I.

601
00:32:54.967 --> 00:32:59.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm going to win this one, Jake.
You know what the best part is?

602
00:32:59.566 --> 00:33:03.924  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I beat Odo. I finally beat him.

603
00:33:04.964 --> 00:33:07.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jake, I did it. I've beat him.

604
00:33:11.202 --> 00:33:13.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, he looks happy. He should be.

605
00:33:13.881 --> 00:33:16.121  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's about to make
his biggest profit of the year.

606
00:33:19.240 --> 00:33:20.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know, Odo.

607
00:33:21.798 --> 00:33:24.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You sure you want to let him get away
with smuggling Denevan crystals?

608
00:33:24.238 --> 00:33:25.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I owe him one.

609
00:33:26.318 --> 00:33:30.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So he'll get this one, but just this one.

610
00:33:33.235 --> 00:33:36.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why is it every time
I think I have you figured out

611
00:33:36.674 --> 00:33:38.394  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you do something to surprise me?

612
00:33:38.674 --> 00:33:39.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Like tonight.

613
00:33:40.154 --> 00:33:43.753  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Where did you get the idea to celebrate
our one-month anniversary in Paris?

614
00:33:44.553 --> 00:33:49.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, some mysteries
are better left unsolved.

615
00:34:04.786 --> 00:34:08.185  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want a complete scan of that barrier
but use passive sensors only, gentlemen.

616
00:34:08.265 --> 00:34:10.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
An active scan is what triggered
the destruction of the <i>Olympia.</i>

617
00:34:10.905 --> 00:34:11.904  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aye, sir.

618
00:34:11.984 --> 00:34:13.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It appears to be an exogenic field

619
00:34:13.464 --> 00:34:15.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
generated by the unstable
elements in the planet's core.

620
00:34:17.382 --> 00:34:20.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Captain Cusak just lost consciousness.
She's in the last stages of CO2 poisoning.

621
00:34:20.821 --> 00:34:21.861  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If she's got any chance at all

622
00:34:21.941 --> 00:34:23.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we have to get her to Sick Bay
in the next 45 minutes.

623
00:34:25.100 --> 00:34:27.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
O'BRIEN: Captain, there's no way
the <i>Defiant </i>can penetrate the barrier.

624
00:34:28.339 --> 00:34:31.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The energy's composed
of subspace metreon radiation.

625
00:34:31.658 --> 00:34:33.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If we get anywhere near it

626
00:34:33.218 --> 00:34:35.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the dilithium matrix
in the warp core will collapse

627
00:34:35.497 --> 00:34:36.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and we'll be pulled down
onto the planet's surface

628
00:34:36.976 --> 00:34:38.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
just like the <i>Olympia.</i>

629
00:34:46.614 --> 00:34:49.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Options?
-Could we beam through it?

630
00:34:49.173 --> 00:34:50.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No. We can't get close enough
to the barrier

631
00:34:50.972 --> 00:34:51.932  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to initiate transport.

632
00:34:52.692 --> 00:34:53.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about a shuttlepod?

633
00:34:53.612 --> 00:34:55.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Their impulse engines
don't use antimatter.

634
00:34:55.571 --> 00:34:58.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It is unlikely that a shuttle
could withstand

635
00:34:58.904 --> 00:35:00.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the gravimetric stresses
that are within the barrier.

636
00:35:00.569 --> 00:35:02.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Unlikely but not impossible.

637
00:35:04.528 --> 00:35:06.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I didn't come all this way to give up.

638
00:35:07.480 --> 00:35:08.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll take the risk.

639
00:35:08.127 --> 00:35:11.367  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Doctor, Mr. O'Brien, you're with me.
Mr. Worf, you have the Bridge.

640
00:35:11.726 --> 00:35:12.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WORF: Aye, sir.

641
00:35:34.599 --> 00:35:37.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sisko to <i>Defiant.</i>
We're preparing to enter the barrier.

642
00:35:37.359 --> 00:35:39.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WORF:<i> Acknowledged. Good luck, Captain.</i>

643
00:35:39.278 --> 00:35:40.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you, Commander.

644
00:35:44.196 --> 00:35:45.796  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shields down to 73 percent.

645
00:35:47.956 --> 00:35:50.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Primary power grid off-line.
Switching to backups.

646
00:35:50.275 --> 00:35:51.914  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shields at 50 percent.

647
00:35:52.749 --> 00:35:53.873  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're losing the navigational computer.

648
00:35:53.954 --> 00:35:55.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
BASHIR: Secondary nav comp on line.

649
00:35:55.873 --> 00:35:57.729  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're coming out of it.

650
00:36:03.951 --> 00:36:05.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damage report.

651
00:36:06.305 --> 00:36:08.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Some buckling
in the starboard hull plating

652
00:36:08.269 --> 00:36:09.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but otherwise, we're fine.

653
00:36:09.788 --> 00:36:10.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Scan the planet, Doctor.

654
00:36:11.468 --> 00:36:13.947  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not showing any life sign.

655
00:36:15.147 --> 00:36:18.666  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Wait. I found the crash site...
and the cave.

656
00:36:18.746 --> 00:36:20.945  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
SISKO: Is there somewhere
we can set down nearby?

657
00:36:21.254 --> 00:36:21.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

658
00:36:22.657 --> 00:36:24.464  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-How are we for time?
-It's going to be tight.

659
00:36:24.545 --> 00:36:25.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've got to get her in the shuttle

660
00:36:25.784 --> 00:36:27.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and back on the ship in 20 minutes.

661
00:37:14.689 --> 00:37:16.249  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Still no life readings.

662
00:37:17.688 --> 00:37:20.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This has to be the only direction
she could have been headed in.

663
00:37:32.604 --> 00:37:33.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
BASHIR: Over here.

664
00:37:35.443 --> 00:37:37.402  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( <i>tricorder beeping </i>)

665
00:37:47.400 --> 00:37:48.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was a human female...

666
00:37:49.479 --> 00:37:55.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Fifty one years of age at time of death.
Cause of death

667
00:37:56.117 --> 00:37:57.237  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
carbon dioxide poisoning.

668
00:37:58.436 --> 00:38:01.636  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
SISKO: It can't be Lisa.
That woman's been dead for years.

669
00:38:02.595 --> 00:38:05.954  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
BASHIR: Three years and two months
but all the evidence fits.

670
00:38:06.354 --> 00:38:10.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Age, rank... the way she died.

671
00:38:12.712 --> 00:38:16.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If she's been dead for three years
how has she been talking to us?

672
00:38:16.951 --> 00:38:18.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It must have something
to do with the energy barrier.

673
00:38:19.909 --> 00:38:23.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When her subspace radio signal
passed through the metreon radiation

674
00:38:23.669 --> 00:38:27.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
in the barrier, the signal somehow
time-shifted into the future.

675
00:38:27.548 --> 00:38:30.707  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then when you sent the return signal?
It went through the barrier

676
00:38:30.866 --> 00:38:32.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and traveled back in time in the same way.

677
00:38:34.425 --> 00:38:36.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've been talking
to someone from the past?

678
00:38:39.984 --> 00:38:41.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So what do we do now?

679
00:38:44.143 --> 00:38:45.262  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We should bury her.

680
00:38:48.141 --> 00:38:53.219  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, not here. Not alone in this cave.

681
00:38:54.739 --> 00:38:58.539  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'll take her back with us...
give her a proper burial...

682
00:38:59.338 --> 00:39:00.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
among friends.

683
00:39:12.454 --> 00:39:14.373  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( muted conversation )

684
00:39:14.854 --> 00:39:18.252  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's called an Irish wake.
It's a way to memorialize a death

685
00:39:18.332 --> 00:39:19.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and celebrate life at the same time.

686
00:39:20.371 --> 00:39:21.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are we supposed to do?

687
00:39:22.131 --> 00:39:27.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, drink, sing songs...
Laugh, cry, talk about the deceased.

688
00:39:28.489 --> 00:39:30.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It sounds almost Klingon.

689
00:39:35.727 --> 00:39:36.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey.

690
00:39:37.474 --> 00:39:38.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, yourself.

691
00:39:39.766 --> 00:39:41.446  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When this is over...

692
00:39:42.765 --> 00:39:46.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want to talk to you about something,
something that's been on my mind.

693
00:39:46.444 --> 00:39:47.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay.

694
00:39:48.603 --> 00:39:49.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Um, is it about me?

695
00:39:50.163 --> 00:39:52.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, it--it's about me, actually.

696
00:39:53.202 --> 00:39:54.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, that's a relief.

697
00:39:56.103 --> 00:40:00.399  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want to try to explain
about my behavior lately.

698
00:40:00.799 --> 00:40:01.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh...

699
00:40:02.239 --> 00:40:05.878  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sounds good to me.
But we'll talk about it over dinner.

700
00:40:06.758 --> 00:40:07.598  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You cook.

701
00:40:09.357 --> 00:40:10.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's a deal.

702
00:40:11.396 --> 00:40:13.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
BASHIR: I, um...
( clears throat ) I just wanted to say

703
00:40:13.835 --> 00:40:14.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that, um...

704
00:40:15.635 --> 00:40:19.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
although I only talked with her
for a very short time

705
00:40:20.153 --> 00:40:23.233  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I really admired Lisa Cusak.

706
00:40:24.233 --> 00:40:25.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I cared about her
and I'm going to miss her.

707
00:40:27.831 --> 00:40:28.791  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And another thing.

708
00:40:29.951 --> 00:40:32.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Contrary to public opinion

709
00:40:33.149 --> 00:40:36.429  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am not the arrogant, self-absorbed

710
00:40:36.509 --> 00:40:39.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
God-like doctor that I appear
to be on occasion.

711
00:40:41.587 --> 00:40:44.146  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why don't I hear anybody
objecting to that statement?

712
00:40:45.506 --> 00:40:47.465  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I will if you insist.

713
00:40:47.545 --> 00:40:50.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I insist.
-Then I object.

714
00:40:50.625 --> 00:40:53.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you, Miles Edward O'Brien.

715
00:40:55.383 --> 00:40:59.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No, I have a heart
and I really care about all of you

716
00:41:00.581 --> 00:41:04.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
even though sometimes it would appear
that I care more about my work.

717
00:41:06.980 --> 00:41:09.219  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
To the woman who, uh, taught me

718
00:41:09.419 --> 00:41:12.378  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that it is sometimes necessary
to say these things,

719
00:41:13.982 --> 00:41:14.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lisa Cusak.

720
00:41:14.857 --> 00:41:16.776  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-To Lisa.
-To Lisa.

721
00:41:23.774 --> 00:41:28.413  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I never shook her hand...
and I never saw her face...

722
00:41:29.893 --> 00:41:34.132  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but she, she made me laugh...
and she made me weep.

723
00:41:35.851 --> 00:41:39.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She was all by herself
and I was surrounded by my friends.

724
00:41:40.250 --> 00:41:42.609  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yet I felt more alone than she did.

725
00:41:44.208 --> 00:41:47.487  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've grown apart, the lot of us.

726
00:41:47.607 --> 00:41:50.869  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We didn't mean for it to happen
but it did.

727
00:41:51.766 --> 00:41:55.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The war changed us, pulled us apart.

728
00:41:57.285 --> 00:42:00.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lisa Cusak was my friend...

729
00:42:01.443 --> 00:42:05.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but you are also my friends
and I want my friends in my life

730
00:42:06.425 --> 00:42:09.681  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
because someday we're going to wake up
and we're going to find

731
00:42:09.761 --> 00:42:14.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that someone is missing from this circle
and on that day, we're going to mourn...

732
00:42:15.879 --> 00:42:18.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and we shouldn't have to mourn alone.

733
00:42:19.598 --> 00:42:22.917  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
To Lisa and the sweet sound of her voice.

